results.overview: P.S. 23 is a small school where we Believe in the success of ALL learners. We offer a vibrant Kindergarten program, where learning comes to life! Our dedicated teachers create a nurturing environment that fosters curiosity and creativity. We have a Science Technology Engineering Arts Mathematics (STEAM) focused program which prepares students to be successful in our rapidly changing society. Students learn computer coding and programming, work in our Hydroponics Science Lab and are exposed to various Arts mediums. Central to our curriculum is the iRead program, specifically designed to diminish the number of students with dyslexia and support all young learners as they develop essential reading skills. As one of only eight schools in the city implementing this innovative program, we offer engaging activities and personalized support that empower our students to become confident readers. For families in need, we offer an after school program run by our Community Based Organization the St. Nick’s Alliance . Join us in nurturing a love for learning that will last a lifetime! You can click the following link (or copy and paste) to see more about us: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Pfy6PArLsWCQcyuzPYFTdbPJL_peabrf/view?usp=drive_link The Intensive Reading Education and Development (IREAD) program is a literacy program, in an integrated co-teaching setting where students receive focused and individualized instruction through a reading intervention that is provided during all subjects to support literacy, language, and speech skills. For more information, speak with your CSE or IEP team and refer to schools.nyc.gov/SpecializedPrograms.
